  m_Paragraphs:
    m_Items:
    - m_Type: 0
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: Casting a Ray in a Direction
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: "Now we need to create a new <doc>Ray</doc> which has an
          origin of the player\u2019s position, and a direction pointing from the
          player to the mouse (you should have seen this vector maths for getting
          a direction between two points in the previous practical on behaviours):\r\n<code>\nRay2D
          rayToMouse = new Ray2D(transform.position, mousePositionInWorldSpace -
          transform.position);\r\n</code>\nUsing the <doc>Physics2D.RaycastAll</doc>
          function, we can get an array of objects that the ray hits in that direction,
          and use the handy <asset>RaycastUtils</asset> class I have written for
          you to debug the raycast results:\r\n<code>\nRaycastHit2D[] hitObjects
          = Physics2D.RaycastAll(rayToMouse.origin, rayToMouse.direction, 100, layerMask);\r\nRaycastUtils.DebugHitInfo(hitObjects);\r\n</code>\nHopefully
          you can see that <doc>Physics2D.RaycastAll</doc> has 4 parameters:\n- the
          origin of the ray\n- the direction of the ray\n- the maximum distance to
          fire the ray\n- the layer mask of things to hit"
